    • Method Detail

      • setSearchArgsExpression

        public void setSearchArgsExpression(org.springframework.expression.Expression searchArgsExpression)
        An expression that is used to build the search; must resolve to a SearchParameters object, or a String, in which case the default page size of 20 is applied, or a list of up to 4 arguments, such as "{payload, headers.pageSize, headers.sinceId, headers.maxId}". The first (required) argument must resolve to a String (query), the optional arguments must resolve to an Number and represent the page size, sinceId, and maxId respectively. Refer to the 'Spring Social Twitter' documentation for more details.

        When using a SearchParameters directly, it is not necessary to include the package: "new SearchParameters("#foo").count(20)").

        Default: "payload".

        Parameters:
        searchArgsExpression - The expression.
